11
00:00:50,251 --> 00:00:52,853
- Hey, Mom.
- Hey, honey.
How you doing?

12
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:54,822
Let me guess... you
have to work late tonight

13
00:00:54,855 --> 00:00:56,824
And you're not gonna
be back until after 10:00.

14
00:00:56,857 --> 00:00:59,660
I'm so sorry.
I know I promised to take
you out to dinner tonight,

15
00:00:59,693 --> 00:01:01,862
But we just got slammed.

16
00:01:01,895 --> 00:01:04,398
There is some Chinese food
in the 'fridge, though.

17
00:01:04,432 --> 00:01:06,200
So how was school?

18
00:01:06,234 --> 00:01:09,537
It was incredible.

19
00:01:09,570 --> 00:01:12,440
My teacher loved
the high contrast photo
I took downtown.

20
00:01:12,473 --> 00:01:14,475
Oh, yeah,
those were great.

21
00:01:14,508 --> 00:01:17,545
And she thinks
that I should send it
to that festival in Paris.

22
00:01:17,578 --> 00:01:20,314
- Wow!
- Let's go to Europe.

23
00:01:20,348 --> 00:01:23,151
- You and me?
- Yeah, we can go
to the festival,

24
00:01:23,184 --> 00:01:25,853
Pick up the award
and then hit the road
in a convertible.

25
00:01:25,886 --> 00:01:27,855
Ha! Okay, I'm in.

26
00:01:27,888 --> 00:01:30,824
Now we just need
to win the lottery
to pay for the trip.

27
00:01:30,858 --> 00:01:33,894
Hey, did you pick up
the mail today?

28
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:36,797
- Uh-uh.
- Well, why don't
you go downstairs

29
00:01:36,830 --> 00:01:39,867
And, you know,
see what's down there?

30
00:01:39,900 --> 00:01:42,403
No, you did not
get that lens that
I was looking at.

31
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:44,205
That is way too expensive.

32
00:01:44,238 --> 00:01:47,508
Hey, let me decide
what is too expensive.
Just go.

33
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:49,877
Check the mail.

34
00:01:55,649 --> 00:01:58,152
- Open the door.
Open the door.
- No!

35
00:01:58,186 --> 00:02:00,754
- Oh, my God. Jodi!
I'm calling 9-1-1.
- You come here right now!

36
00:02:00,788 --> 00:02:02,823
Get out
of the apartment now!

37
00:02:02,856 --> 00:02:04,892
- Man: Come here!
- Jodi: Please let me go!
Get out!

38
00:02:04,925 --> 00:02:06,927
- Jodi!
- Mom!

39
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:08,829
My daughter is getting
attacked right now.

40
00:02:08,862 --> 00:02:11,399
- 52822 Loma Verde Avenue...
- What you doing, huh?

41
00:02:11,432 --> 00:02:13,167
Apartment 18,
West Hollywood.

42
00:02:13,201 --> 00:02:17,405
Oh, my God!
Send somebody fast.
Jodi, no! No!

43
00:02:17,438 --> 00:02:19,773
Stop it!
Get away from her!

44
00:02:19,807 --> 00:02:22,676
Oh, my God. No!

45
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:56,710
(Sighs) Okay,
this is the last of it.

46
00:03:00,481 --> 00:03:03,317
Oh, I cannot wait to show you
the new bedspread I bought.

47
00:03:03,351 --> 00:03:04,585
Come on.

48
00:03:28,976 --> 00:03:32,246
I think I have
unpacked enough for us

49
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:35,383
To at least have
breakfast tomorrow.

50
00:03:35,416 --> 00:03:38,886
I have to get up at
4:00 so I can be at
the hospital by 6:00,

51
00:03:38,919 --> 00:03:40,488
So I'm gonna go to bed.

52
00:03:40,521 --> 00:03:41,955
Good night, baby.

53
00:03:43,891 --> 00:03:46,627
Did you lock
the back door?

54
00:03:46,660 --> 00:03:48,028
Yeah.

55
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:49,930
What about the windows?

56
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:53,701
Yes, honey.

57
00:03:53,734 --> 00:03:55,869
Hey...

58
00:03:55,903 --> 00:03:59,440
This place is gonna
be really great.

59
00:03:59,473 --> 00:04:03,010
I don't know how
I'm gonna pay for it,
but it's worth it.

60
00:04:03,043 --> 00:04:05,779
This summer we're
gonna have so much fun.

61
00:04:05,813 --> 00:04:09,783
And then in the fall,
you are gonna go to
a terrific new high school

62
00:04:09,817 --> 00:04:12,420
And meet a bunch
of new friends.

63
00:04:15,956 --> 00:04:18,592
Sweetie, the police shot
that awful man.

64
00:04:18,626 --> 00:04:21,695
He can't hurt you
anymore.

65
00:04:21,729 --> 00:04:25,032
This is a safe neighborhood.

66
00:04:25,065 --> 00:04:27,000
We're gonna be okay here.

67
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:31,972
- Good night.
- Don't stay up too late.

68
00:04:43,517 --> 00:04:46,687
(Wind blowing)

69
00:04:48,989 --> 00:04:51,492
(Thumping)

70
00:04:58,632 --> 00:05:02,370
(Tapping)

71
00:05:07,375 --> 00:05:09,410
Mom. Mom, wake up.

72
00:05:09,443 --> 00:05:10,944
Andrea:
What's the matter?

73
00:05:10,978 --> 00:05:12,913
- Did you hear that?
- (tapping continues)

74
00:05:12,946 --> 00:05:14,782
I think that's
the wind, honey.

75
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:17,585
No, there's someone
at the door.

76
00:05:17,618 --> 00:05:20,888
(Sighs)
Do you realize
what time it is?

77
00:05:20,921 --> 00:05:23,657
Put that down.

78
00:05:26,126 --> 00:05:28,496
(Tapping)

79
00:05:30,498 --> 00:05:33,867
See, it's nothing
to worry about.

80
00:05:35,102 --> 00:05:37,771
Will you sleep
in my room tonight?

81
00:05:38,839 --> 00:05:40,574
Sure, honey.

82
00:05:53,587 --> 00:05:56,724
(Music blaring
over radio)

83
00:05:56,757 --> 00:05:59,860
- Man: Fire it up.
- (engine turns over)

84
00:06:04,498 --> 00:06:07,601
- Man #2: Yeah!
- (engine revving)

85
00:06:07,635 --> 00:06:10,070
- What do you think?
- Give it a little more gas.

86
00:06:10,103 --> 00:06:12,573
Hey, give it
a little more gas.

87
00:06:12,606 --> 00:06:15,876
- (Engine revs)
- Nice.

88
00:06:15,909 --> 00:06:18,546
- How's that?
- (camera whirring)

89
00:06:18,579 --> 00:06:19,980
- A little more.
- (camera shutter clicks)

90
00:06:20,013 --> 00:06:22,716
- Now we're
getting somewhere.
- Yeah!

91
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:25,419
Man #3:
Come on, honey,
you don't have to leave.

92
00:06:25,453 --> 00:06:28,021
Are you sure we can't
talk about this?

93
00:06:28,055 --> 00:06:29,657
Come on.

94
00:06:31,859 --> 00:06:33,994
Out of my way.

95
00:06:34,027 --> 00:06:36,063
- Man #2: How's that?
- Man: That's good.

96
00:06:36,096 --> 00:06:38,866
That's good!
That's working now.

97
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:41,802
- (Engine revving)
- There. Nice, nice! I love it,
I love it, I love it!

98
00:06:41,835 --> 00:06:44,171
- Awesome!
- Man #2: Whoo-hoo!

99
00:06:44,204 --> 00:06:47,441
That's what
I'm talking about.

100
00:06:49,543 --> 00:06:51,645
Man:
Uh-oh, turn it off.

101
00:06:53,647 --> 00:06:55,849
- Man: You owe me 100 bucks.
- Woman: Nick.

102
00:06:55,883 --> 00:06:58,085
Aw, jeez.
Mrs. Miller.

103
00:06:58,118 --> 00:07:01,489
I know what you're gonna say
and I'm done for the day.

104
00:07:01,522 --> 00:07:04,758
It's not about today.
It's about tomorrow
and the next day

105
00:07:04,792 --> 00:07:06,794
And the next month.
You see, I work from home.

106
00:07:06,827 --> 00:07:09,497
So I need to be able
to have a phone conversation
with a client

107
00:07:09,530 --> 00:07:11,832
- and be able to hear them.
- I'm sorry, all right?

108
00:07:11,865 --> 00:07:13,534
I'm just doing a favor
for some friends of mine.

109
00:07:13,567 --> 00:07:14,902
- A favor?
- Yeah.

110
00:07:14,935 --> 00:07:16,604
You're running a business
out of your garage.

111
00:07:16,637 --> 00:07:18,606
- I'm not running a business.
- Come on, Nick.

112
00:07:18,639 --> 00:07:20,073
Woman #2: Aunt Lisa, relax.
It's not a big deal.

113
00:07:20,107 --> 00:07:22,743
Look at this place.
I mean, are you kidding me?

114
00:07:22,776 --> 00:07:25,112
Do you have any idea what
you're doing to the property
values around here?

115
00:07:25,145 --> 00:07:27,047
Nick: I'll tell you this.
This is one piece
of property

116
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:29,650
That you don't have your
hands on yet, Mrs. Miller.

117
00:07:29,683 --> 00:07:33,186
All right, I've asked you
nicely. Next time I'm
calling the cops.

118
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:36,123
Go right ahead.
I'm shaking in my boots,
Mrs. Miller.

119
00:07:36,156 --> 00:07:38,892
- Bossing everybody around.
- Lisa: Ugh, this is
ridiculous.

120
00:07:38,926 --> 00:07:42,563
- Man: I agree.
- Hey, how are you?

121
00:07:42,596 --> 00:07:44,732
- Great.
- Glad to hear it.

122
00:07:52,606 --> 00:07:54,908
- Lisa: Kristen.
- Coming.

123
00:08:01,281 --> 00:08:02,816
Hey.

124
00:08:05,185 --> 00:08:07,054
- (Indistinct chatter)
- (shutter clicking)

125
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:27,140
(Gasps)

126
00:08:48,228 --> 00:08:51,298
(Whirring and clicking)

127
00:09:18,225 --> 00:09:20,227
(Telephone ringing)

128
00:09:28,702 --> 00:09:30,337
- (beeps)
- Hello?

129
00:09:32,339 --> 00:09:34,107
Hello?

130
00:09:41,248 --> 00:09:42,282
(Beeps)

131
00:10:05,673 --> 00:10:08,308
(Doorbell rings)

132
00:10:12,913 --> 00:10:15,015
(Doorbell continues
ringing)

133
00:10:30,330 --> 00:10:32,332
(Jodi sighs)

134
00:10:36,937 --> 00:10:40,007
Hi, I'm Lisa Miller.
I live across the street.

135
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:42,342
I just wanted to welcome
you to the neighborhood.

136
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,411
Hi, I'm Jodi.

137
00:10:44,444 --> 00:10:46,780
Hi, Jodi.
I made you some cookies.

138
00:10:46,814 --> 00:10:48,782
Thank you.

139
00:10:48,816 --> 00:10:51,018
So are your parents home?

140
00:10:51,051 --> 00:10:52,886
I would like to say hello.

141
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,922
It's just my mom.
She's at work.

142
00:10:54,955 --> 00:10:58,158
Okay, well, tell her
I dropped by, okay?

143
00:10:59,292 --> 00:11:02,896
Are you all right?

144
00:11:02,930 --> 00:11:06,399
- Sweetie, what's the matter?
- Someone just stole
my camera.

145
00:11:06,433 --> 00:11:09,002
What? Are you serious?

146
00:11:09,036 --> 00:11:10,904
This area is so safe.

147
00:11:10,938 --> 00:11:13,306
I mean, we never have
burglaries out here.

148
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:15,442
I'm sorry.
I'm just a little
freaked out right now.

149
00:11:15,475 --> 00:11:18,045
Don't apologize.

150
00:11:18,078 --> 00:11:20,113
You wanna come
over to my house?

151
00:11:20,147 --> 00:11:22,215
You can stay with us
until she gets back.

152
00:11:22,249 --> 00:11:25,452
No, that's very kind of you,
but I'll be okay.

153
00:11:25,485 --> 00:11:29,422
Listen, why don't
you and your mom
come over tomorrow?

154
00:11:29,456 --> 00:11:31,458
You can have lunch with
me and my niece Kristen.

155
00:11:31,491 --> 00:11:33,861
You'd like her.

156
00:11:33,894 --> 00:11:35,796
Okay, I'll ask my mom.

157
00:11:35,829 --> 00:11:37,097
Great.

158
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:40,100
Just let me know.
Here's my number, okay?

159
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:41,234
Thank you.

160
00:12:34,521 --> 00:12:37,190
Andrea: Are you sure
you didn't misplace it?

161
00:12:37,224 --> 00:12:39,159
I mean, look at this.

162
00:12:39,192 --> 00:12:41,428
Yes, I looked everywhere.

163
00:12:41,461 --> 00:12:43,496
I think we should
call the police.

164
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:45,933
Let's get this place
cleaned up.

165
00:12:45,966 --> 00:12:48,435
If we still don't find it,
I'll buy you a new one.

166
00:12:48,468 --> 00:12:50,470
Mom, I don't want you
spending that kind of money.

167
00:12:50,503 --> 00:12:53,841
- Don't worry.
I can afford it.
- No, you can't.

168
00:12:53,874 --> 00:12:56,176
You're always saying
how expensive it is
to live here.

169
00:12:56,209 --> 00:12:59,512
I'm telling you,
somebody came into
the backyard.

170
00:12:59,546 --> 00:13:03,516
We've only been here
two days and already you're
saying we've been robbed?

171
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:06,053
Yes, and I want
to report this.

172
00:13:06,086 --> 00:13:08,922
First, let's clean up
the house, okay?

173
00:13:08,956 --> 00:13:12,125
Okay, what time do they
want us over for lunch?

174
00:13:14,261 --> 00:13:16,029
(Music blaring
over radio)

175
00:13:23,904 --> 00:13:25,272
(Engine revs)

176
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:27,574
So where did you live
before you moved here?

177
00:13:27,607 --> 00:13:31,511
- West Hollywood.
- Oh, I love West Hollywood.
Why'd you guys leave?

178
00:13:31,544 --> 00:13:32,812
No!

179
00:13:33,947 --> 00:13:35,582
We had a condo.

180
00:13:35,615 --> 00:13:38,118
We needed more space.

181
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:41,889
- Mm-hmm.
- So, Kristen, I take it
you live in LA?

182
00:13:41,922 --> 00:13:44,024
- No, I live here.
- Oh, I thought you were

183
00:13:44,057 --> 00:13:45,859
Just visiting
your Aunt Lisa
for the summer.

184
00:13:45,893 --> 00:13:48,228
This is my home now.
My parents are gone.

185
00:13:49,362 --> 00:13:51,431
Her mom passed away
last year.

186
00:13:51,464 --> 00:13:54,101
I am so sorry.

187
00:13:54,134 --> 00:13:56,870
I asked Kristen
if she would wanna
come live with me,

188
00:13:56,904 --> 00:14:00,540
And well,
I'm just glad
she said yes.

189
00:14:00,573 --> 00:14:03,877
You know, you should
take Jodi with you
next weekend.

190
00:14:03,911 --> 00:14:05,445
That's a great idea.
You'd love it.

191
00:14:05,478 --> 00:14:07,514
What?

192
00:14:07,547 --> 00:14:10,350
Our church.
They have this retreat.
It's up Angeles Crest.

193
00:14:10,383 --> 00:14:14,021
It's so fun.
They have hiking and volleyball
and all the fun stuff.

194
00:14:14,054 --> 00:14:16,223
Yeah, the van's gonna pick
me up next Saturday morning.

195
00:14:16,256 --> 00:14:18,625
Okay, I'll think about it.

196
00:14:18,658 --> 00:14:20,928
You should go.
That sounds really great.

197
00:14:20,961 --> 00:14:22,629
Mom, I said I will
think about it.

198
00:14:22,662 --> 00:14:25,232
- (Engine turns over)
- Andrea: Okay.

199
00:14:25,265 --> 00:14:28,268
(Engine revving)

200
00:14:28,301 --> 00:14:31,038
Not again.

201
00:14:31,071 --> 00:14:32,405
Have you talked
to his parents?

202
00:14:32,439 --> 00:14:34,241
He's a single father.

203
00:14:34,274 --> 00:14:37,344
He's in the oil
business in Dubai.

204
00:14:37,377 --> 00:14:40,914
That's enough.
I am so sorry, Andrea.

205
00:14:40,948 --> 00:14:44,017
- Aunt Lisa,
what are you doing?
- Calling the police.

206
00:14:44,051 --> 00:14:46,886
(Touch tones beeping)

207
00:14:50,991 --> 00:14:52,993
(Engine revving)

208
00:14:59,732 --> 00:15:01,701
Hi, I'm the one
that called the police.

209
00:15:01,734 --> 00:15:03,403
- I'm Lisa Miller.
- Officer Weiland.

210
00:15:03,436 --> 00:15:05,505
How you doing today?
You Nick?

211
00:15:05,538 --> 00:15:07,574
- Yeah.
- Nick, you wanna step out
of the car for me?

212
00:15:07,607 --> 00:15:09,476
I'm not trying to bother
anybody. I'm working
on my buddy's car.

213
00:15:09,509 --> 00:15:12,145
- He's always a bother.
Always.
- What?!

214
00:15:12,179 --> 00:15:14,314
That guy Nick
stole my camera.

215
00:15:14,347 --> 00:15:16,649
He was the only one around
when I noticed it was missing.

216
00:15:16,683 --> 00:15:19,052
You should go tell the cop.

217
00:15:19,086 --> 00:15:21,621
I'm not gonna introduce myself
to our next door neighbor

218
00:15:21,654 --> 00:15:23,590
By accusing him
of burglary.

219
00:15:23,623 --> 00:15:26,593
Just ask the cop to come over
and we can talk in private.

220
00:15:26,626 --> 00:15:29,129
It doesn't have
to be a big deal.

221
00:15:29,162 --> 00:15:31,098
- Please?
- Okay.
- Thanks.

222
00:15:31,131 --> 00:15:32,465
Weiland: Son, I need
you to calm down.

223
00:15:32,499 --> 00:15:34,401
Just take it
from me, okay?

224
00:15:34,434 --> 00:15:36,003
And if we get
any more complaints,

225
00:15:36,036 --> 00:15:37,437
I'm gonna have to
come back here
and arrest you.

226
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:39,106
- Andrea: Excuse me, Officer.
- Nick: Yeah, yeah, whatever.

227
00:15:39,139 --> 00:15:42,175
Miss Miller,
stay back, please.

228
00:15:42,209 --> 00:15:45,412
I just wanted to talk to
you about something that
happened in our house.

229
00:15:45,445 --> 00:15:48,448
- We live across the street...
- So you think somebody
stole your camera?

230
00:15:48,481 --> 00:15:51,051
Yesterday I was
outside taking pictures

231
00:15:51,084 --> 00:15:53,453
And the phone rang,
so I put the camera down,

232
00:15:53,486 --> 00:15:56,623
Came in to answer it,
and when I went back out,
it was gone.

233
00:15:56,656 --> 00:15:59,692
- What kind of camera is it?
- A DSLR with a 75 to 300
zoom lens.

234
00:15:59,726 --> 00:16:02,629
Is it anything like
that camera out there?

235
00:16:02,662 --> 00:16:04,631
What?!

236
00:16:04,664 --> 00:16:07,534
Officer, I am so sorry
to bother you.

237
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:09,669
Not a problem.
I hope she gets
some great pictures.

238
00:16:09,702 --> 00:16:12,205
- Thank you.
- Okay? All right.

239
00:16:15,408 --> 00:16:18,678
- Well, that was embarrassing.
- Mom, I checked the backyard.

240
00:16:18,711 --> 00:16:22,015
I checked the house, everywhere.
I swear it wasn't there.

241
00:16:22,049 --> 00:16:25,385
- What do you think happened?
- I think Nick stole it
and then put it back.

242
00:16:25,418 --> 00:16:28,755
Why would anybody
do that?

243
00:16:28,788 --> 00:16:31,258
Sweetie,
it's a new house.

244
00:16:31,291 --> 00:16:34,394
It's a new neighborhood.
You're still recovering.

245
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:36,263
What happened to you
at our old apartment,

246
00:16:36,296 --> 00:16:38,331
It's gonna take you
a while to get over that.

247
00:16:41,101 --> 00:16:43,703
I still see him.

248
00:16:43,736 --> 00:16:46,206
- In your dreams?
- In my mind.

249
00:16:46,239 --> 00:16:50,710
Every time
I go in a dark room
or I open a door,

250
00:16:50,743 --> 00:16:55,682
It's like he's gonna
be there, but he's not.

251
00:16:55,715 --> 00:16:57,417
I never should have
worked late that night.

252
00:16:57,450 --> 00:16:59,586
- Don't say that.
- No, I'm your mother.

253
00:16:59,619 --> 00:17:03,656
I'm supposed to protect you.
I should have been there.

254
00:17:06,226 --> 00:17:09,629
I have to do some shopping.

255
00:17:09,662 --> 00:17:11,264
Do you wanna go with me?

256
00:17:11,298 --> 00:17:13,500
I just wanna
check my camera.

257
00:17:13,533 --> 00:17:15,168
Okay, sweetie.

258
00:17:36,756 --> 00:17:40,793
(Touch tones beeping)

259
00:17:40,827 --> 00:17:44,564
(Rings)

260
00:17:44,597 --> 00:17:47,434
Man: Hello?

261
00:17:47,467 --> 00:17:49,369
Hello.

262
00:17:50,770 --> 00:17:54,441
Um, who am I speaking with?

263
00:17:54,474 --> 00:17:57,110
This is Nick.
Who is this?

264
00:17:57,144 --> 00:17:58,545
(Beeps)

265
00:18:00,547 --> 00:18:03,316
(Cell phone rings)

266
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:05,452
- Hey.
- Mom, I can prove it.

267
00:18:05,485 --> 00:18:07,820
- Prove what, honey?
- That Nick stole my camera.

268
00:18:07,854 --> 00:18:10,690
Remember when I got a call
and there was nobody
on the line?

269
00:18:10,723 --> 00:18:13,126
- Well, I checked
the phone records...
- (knock on door)

270
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:14,161
Hold on.

271
00:18:18,431 --> 00:18:20,333
Oh, my God.
He's at the door.

272
00:18:20,367 --> 00:18:22,369
You don't have to open it.
Do you want me to come home?

273
00:18:22,402 --> 00:18:24,704
I will if you want me to.

274
00:18:24,737 --> 00:18:27,274
In fact, honey,
I'm just gonna come home.
I'll be there in ten minutes.

275
00:18:27,307 --> 00:18:30,443
- (Knock on door)
- No, it's okay.
I'll just see what he wants.

276
00:18:30,477 --> 00:18:32,279
- Jodi.
- Mom, don't worry.
I'll be all right.

277
00:18:32,312 --> 00:18:33,880
(Clicks)

278
00:18:35,248 --> 00:18:36,883
You called my house?

279
00:18:36,916 --> 00:18:39,319
Did you call me?

280
00:18:39,352 --> 00:18:42,155
Why did you steal my camera?

281
00:18:42,189 --> 00:18:44,891
Because you were taking
pictures of me and you
didn't ask me if you could.

282
00:18:44,924 --> 00:18:46,626
How did you get
our house number?

283
00:18:46,659 --> 00:18:49,396
The internet.
Reverse address.

284
00:18:49,429 --> 00:18:53,233
So you called our house,
made me go inside to answer
it, and then hopped the fence

285
00:18:53,266 --> 00:18:56,436
- and stole my camera?
- That's right.

286
00:18:56,469 --> 00:18:58,471
- You're good.
- Then you put it on the porch

287
00:18:58,505 --> 00:19:00,240
- and made me look
like an idiot.
- No, no, no.

288
00:19:00,273 --> 00:19:02,742
Well, I didn't mean
to make you look
like an idiot.

289
00:19:02,775 --> 00:19:05,312
But if that happened,
I'll consider it a bonus.

290
00:19:05,345 --> 00:19:09,882
- I'm going to tell
the cops what you did.
- Wow! First Lisa and now you.

291
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:12,419
Terrific. Go right ahead
and call the cops.

292
00:19:12,452 --> 00:19:15,822
And I'll show them the pictures
you took of me, half naked.

293
00:19:15,855 --> 00:19:19,726
Yeah, I downloaded
your camera files
onto my hard drive.

294
00:19:19,759 --> 00:19:22,929
While I'm at it, I'll show
the rest of the neighborhood
the pictures you took of them.

295
00:19:22,962 --> 00:19:25,798
Ted's wife across the street,
she's a lawyer.

296
00:19:25,832 --> 00:19:27,734
She'd love to see them.

297
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:31,271
So you sure you wanna
call the cops?

298
00:19:31,304 --> 00:19:34,374
I just wanna call it even.

299
00:19:34,407 --> 00:19:36,743
Even.

300
00:19:39,312 --> 00:19:40,480
I'm Nick.

301
00:19:44,484 --> 00:19:46,486
(Sighing)

302
00:19:52,492 --> 00:19:54,427
(Horn honks)

303
00:19:58,398 --> 00:20:00,633
- Kristen: Hey.
- Nick: Okay,
Tuesday sounds good.

304
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:03,436
- Yeah.
- Woman: This is gonna
be so much fun.

305
00:20:03,470 --> 00:20:07,307
- Nick: Yeah, 11:00 a.m.
- Kristen: Hey!

306
00:20:07,340 --> 00:20:09,242
- I'll be there.
- Man on phone: Talk
to you later.

307
00:20:09,276 --> 00:20:10,343
Bye.

308
00:20:28,961 --> 00:20:31,398
(Cell phone rings)

309
00:20:33,933 --> 00:20:36,569
- Hey, Mom.
- Hi, honey, what are you doing?

310
00:20:36,603 --> 00:20:38,771
- Just testing out my new lens.
- Cool!

311
00:20:38,805 --> 00:20:41,474
Well, I'll be done
at the hospital
in about an hour.

312
00:20:41,508 --> 00:20:43,476
- You sure everything's okay?
- (camera shutter clicks)

313
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:45,845
- Everything's fine, Mom.
- Call me if you need me.

314
00:20:45,878 --> 00:20:47,447
- All right.
- Bye.

315
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:49,782
- Bye.
- (beeps)

316
00:21:03,463 --> 00:21:05,498
(Beeps)

317
00:21:19,045 --> 00:21:21,314
(Bell ringing)

318
00:21:34,394 --> 00:21:35,928
I think I just saw someone
in your house.

319
00:21:35,962 --> 00:21:37,397
- What?
- I just saw someone.

320
00:21:37,430 --> 00:21:39,799
Or I thought I did.
Downstairs.

321
00:21:39,832 --> 00:21:41,468
Hold on.
You were watching my house?

322
00:21:41,501 --> 00:21:42,969
I was taking pictures
of the street.

323
00:21:43,002 --> 00:21:45,338
I saw you in your bedroom,
and I looked in the window

324
00:21:45,372 --> 00:21:47,607
And I saw a
shadow of someone.
Are you serious?

325
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,542
Yes, let's just go to my
house and call the police.

326
00:21:49,576 --> 00:21:51,678
No, no, no,
hang on. Hang on.
Just give me a second.

327
00:21:51,711 --> 00:21:53,846
Wait, wait, Lisa, don't.

328
00:22:06,626 --> 00:22:08,361
Are you sure you saw someone?

329
00:22:08,395 --> 00:22:10,963
Yes, it was a shadow.

330
00:22:10,997 --> 00:22:12,599
Male, female?

331
00:22:12,632 --> 00:22:14,967
I don't know.
The shades were closed.

332
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:18,037
Wait here.
I'll check the garage.

333
00:22:52,104 --> 00:22:55,007
There's nobody down here.
Are you sure?

334
00:22:55,041 --> 00:22:58,945
Yes, I'm sure.
At least I thought...

335
00:22:58,978 --> 00:23:02,048
Look, let's just
get out of here.

336
00:23:02,081 --> 00:23:04,016
- I'm gonna check upstairs.
- I'm calling the cops.

337
00:23:04,050 --> 00:23:05,918
No, no, no,
just give me a minute.

338
00:23:34,013 --> 00:23:37,016
(Sighs)
There's nobody here.

339
00:23:37,049 --> 00:23:39,886
Oh, look, look at this.

340
00:23:43,523 --> 00:23:45,625
Is this what you saw?

341
00:23:47,159 --> 00:23:50,162
I must have walked
in front of it.

342
00:23:50,196 --> 00:23:51,698
Maybe.

343
00:23:54,801 --> 00:23:56,168
I'm sure that's what you saw.

344
00:23:58,137 --> 00:23:59,806
I'm sorry to bother you.

345
00:23:59,839 --> 00:24:01,841
Oh, no, no.
Honey, it's okay.

346
00:24:01,874 --> 00:24:04,711
I really appreciate
your concern.

347
00:26:18,678 --> 00:26:20,112
- Man: See you later.
- Bye, guys.

348
00:26:20,146 --> 00:26:21,981
Woman: Bye, Kristen.

349
00:26:22,014 --> 00:26:23,182
Hey.

350
00:26:23,215 --> 00:26:24,617
Hey, Jodi, how's it going?

351
00:26:24,651 --> 00:26:26,853
Good.
Did you have fun?

352
00:26:26,886 --> 00:26:29,155
Yeah, it was so funny.
You have to come with us

353
00:26:29,188 --> 00:26:31,624
The next time we go on one
of these camping trips.

354
00:26:33,192 --> 00:26:35,294
Aunt Lisa, I'm back.

355
00:26:35,327 --> 00:26:38,364
They did this improv show.
It was so hysterical.

356
00:26:38,397 --> 00:26:41,801
This guy talks totally monotone
like he's got one brain cell

357
00:26:41,834 --> 00:26:44,336
And he has a scene partner
who was talking a mile a minute.

358
00:26:44,370 --> 00:26:46,773
Aunt Lisa, are you upstairs?

359
00:26:46,806 --> 00:26:49,175
Anyway, they're on this gurney
and they're acting like
he's giving birth

360
00:26:49,208 --> 00:26:51,911
Completely in drag.
It was so funny.

361
00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:56,916
Jodi.

362
00:26:58,250 --> 00:27:01,187
Jodi, where'd you go?

363
00:27:10,029 --> 00:27:13,199
- Oh, my God.
- Kristen: Are you up here?

364
00:27:13,232 --> 00:27:17,670
- Don't come in.
- Oh, my God.

365
00:27:17,704 --> 00:27:19,305
- Aunt Lisa, what's wrong?
- 9-1-1. What's your emergency?

366
00:27:19,338 --> 00:27:21,340
No, what's wrong with her?
(gasps)

367
00:27:21,373 --> 00:27:23,442
(Stammers)
I need an ambulance.

368
00:27:23,475 --> 00:27:27,847
- 8672, Via Colinas
in Santa Clarita.
- Aunt Lisa, wake up.

369
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:29,348
My friend, she's bleeding.
She's not breathing.

370
00:27:29,381 --> 00:27:31,751
We need an ambulance
right now. Hurry!

371
00:27:39,391 --> 00:27:41,427
(Police radio chatter)

372
00:27:49,936 --> 00:27:52,705
Detective, I saw something
on Saturday night

373
00:27:52,739 --> 00:27:55,241
That I think you
should know about.

374
00:27:55,274 --> 00:27:59,445
I got here as fast
as I could. Oh, my God.
Are you okay?

375
00:27:59,478 --> 00:28:00,947
I was so worried about you.

376
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:03,449
Hi. Detective Franklin.

377
00:28:03,482 --> 00:28:05,918
Andrea Allen,
Jodi's mother.

378
00:28:05,952 --> 00:28:07,386
As you were saying?

379
00:28:07,419 --> 00:28:10,256
I saw someone in the house.

380
00:28:10,289 --> 00:28:12,725
I think it was an intruder.

381
00:28:12,759 --> 00:28:14,393
- About what time?
- Around 10:00.

382
00:28:14,426 --> 00:28:16,228
I was across the street
in my room

383
00:28:16,262 --> 00:28:18,831
Taking some pictures
of the neighborhood.

384
00:28:18,865 --> 00:28:20,266
I saw Lisa
in the upstairs window

385
00:28:20,299 --> 00:28:23,202
And then I saw somebody else
in the downstairs window.

386
00:28:23,235 --> 00:28:26,906
You were taking photographs
of peoples' homes at night?

387
00:28:26,939 --> 00:28:28,440
Yeah, is that illegal?

388
00:28:28,474 --> 00:28:30,843
It's an invasion
of privacy.

389
00:28:30,877 --> 00:28:34,781
Next time you do that,
you should ask your
neighbors for permission.

390
00:28:34,814 --> 00:28:38,818
Anyway, is that the window
with the shades closed?

391
00:28:38,851 --> 00:28:42,121
I saw a shadow,
a silhouette.

392
00:28:42,154 --> 00:28:44,924
That's a long ways
to see at night.

393
00:28:44,957 --> 00:28:46,993
I know what I saw.

394
00:28:47,026 --> 00:28:49,028
Well, did you take a
picture of the shadow?

395
00:28:49,061 --> 00:28:50,997
No, I didn't.

396
00:28:51,030 --> 00:28:55,434
Okay, Jodi, so when you
saw this shadow person,
what did you do then?

397
00:28:55,467 --> 00:28:57,804
I ran over
and I rang the doorbell.

398
00:28:57,837 --> 00:29:00,539
Lisa answered, and we
looked around, but we
didn't find anybody.

399
00:29:00,572 --> 00:29:02,041
Why didn't you
call the police?

400
00:29:02,074 --> 00:29:03,810
Because Lisa didn't
want me to.

401
00:29:03,843 --> 00:29:05,912
She wasn't worried like I was.

402
00:29:05,945 --> 00:29:08,915
I mean, I even tried
calling her this morning
and nobody answered.

403
00:29:08,948 --> 00:29:11,450
And that's why I waited
for Kristen to get home.

404
00:29:11,483 --> 00:29:13,920
I watched the house all day
and Lisa never came out.

405
00:29:13,953 --> 00:29:16,422
Thanks. I'll mention
that in my report.

406
00:29:19,425 --> 00:29:22,494
I think the guy
next door did it. Nick.

407
00:29:22,528 --> 00:29:24,563
Now is that the same
Nick Thompkin

408
00:29:24,596 --> 00:29:27,266
That's running a business out
of his house without a permit?

409
00:29:27,299 --> 00:29:29,135
Yeah.

410
00:29:29,168 --> 00:29:32,138
Lisa called the cops on him
and Nick got really mad at her.

411
00:29:32,171 --> 00:29:34,974
If anyone from the neighborhood
would kill her, it would be him.

412
00:29:35,007 --> 00:29:37,944
Well, we'll talk to him.
We'll be talking to
everybody on this block.

413
00:29:37,977 --> 00:29:40,880
Detective, what do
you think happened?

414
00:29:40,913 --> 00:29:42,815
Well, we don't have
the whole story yet.

415
00:29:42,849 --> 00:29:45,317
There doesn't seem to be
any sign of forced entry.

416
00:29:45,351 --> 00:29:47,253
As far as I can tell,
nothing is stolen.

417
00:29:47,286 --> 00:29:49,822
So right now it looks
like she slipped and fell.

418
00:29:49,856 --> 00:29:51,590
- You're kidding, right?
- Jodi, don't.

419
00:29:51,623 --> 00:29:55,061
When forensics
comes back with their
report in a couple days,

420
00:29:55,094 --> 00:29:57,830
We'll have
a better assessment.

421
00:30:00,366 --> 00:30:03,970
Oh, my God,
Kristen, I'm so sorry.

422
00:30:04,003 --> 00:30:05,905
Come here. Ohh.

423
00:30:05,938 --> 00:30:09,508
Kristen:
Can I stay with you guys
just for a few days?

424
00:30:09,541 --> 00:30:13,312
Yes, of course.
You stay as long
as you need to, okay?

425
00:30:31,998 --> 00:30:34,400
Hi, I'm Detective Ng,
Metro Homicide.

426
00:30:34,433 --> 00:30:36,402
- You live here?
- Yeah.

427
00:30:36,435 --> 00:30:39,005
We're getting statements
from a number of people.

428
00:30:39,038 --> 00:30:41,607
- Do you mind if we ask
you a few questions?
- (Nick clears throat)

429
00:30:43,142 --> 00:30:47,079
Yeah, yeah, sure.
Come in. Right this way.

430
00:30:51,617 --> 00:30:53,953
Andrea:
I'm not going
into work tomorrow, okay?

431
00:30:53,986 --> 00:30:55,888
I'm gonna be here all day.

432
00:30:55,922 --> 00:30:57,456
Thank you, Ms. Allen.

433
00:30:59,025 --> 00:31:02,594
(Kisses)
You try and get some rest.

434
00:31:05,131 --> 00:31:07,533
- I wanna talk to her.
- Let her rest.

435
00:31:07,566 --> 00:31:10,069
But, Mom.

436
00:31:10,102 --> 00:31:12,905
I'm telling you,
somebody was in her
house that night.

437
00:31:12,939 --> 00:31:14,941
Shh.
Keep your voice down.

438
00:31:14,974 --> 00:31:17,876
She doesn't need to hear that.
She's suffering enough.

439
00:31:20,612 --> 00:31:23,916
And why did you incriminate
the boy across the street?

440
00:31:23,950 --> 00:31:28,120
- Well, what if he did do it?
- Then the police will find
evidence to support that.

441
00:31:28,154 --> 00:31:30,456
Will you please
stay out of it?

442
00:31:30,489 --> 00:31:33,059
Let them do their job.
(scoffs)

443
00:31:33,092 --> 00:31:35,294
Can't believe you said
that to the cop.

444
00:31:38,097 --> 00:31:42,168
- Oh, well, I'm sorry
if I embarrassed you, Mom.
- I'm not embarrassed.

445
00:31:42,201 --> 00:31:46,438
Forget the fact that I'm
the one who found Lisa on
the bathroom floor today.

446
00:31:46,472 --> 00:31:49,908
I didn't know I was
supposed to be worried
about how you felt.

447
00:31:51,243 --> 00:31:52,711
I'm sorry.

448
00:31:52,744 --> 00:31:55,181
Just leave me alone.

449
00:31:58,050 --> 00:31:59,051
(Sighs)

450
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:05,024
- I need to talk to you.
- (gasps) You scared me.

451
00:32:05,057 --> 00:32:06,993
I overheard you
talking to your mom.

452
00:32:07,026 --> 00:32:09,061
You saw somebody
in the house Saturday night?

453
00:32:09,095 --> 00:32:10,429
Look, I shouldn't
have said anything.

454
00:32:10,462 --> 00:32:12,331
Please I need
to know what you saw.

455
00:32:14,066 --> 00:32:17,169
Kristen, my mom was right.

456
00:32:17,203 --> 00:32:19,972
And you've been
through enough already.

457
00:32:20,006 --> 00:32:23,209
You don't need
to be worried about this.

458
00:32:26,678 --> 00:32:29,215
It was only a shadow.

459
00:32:29,248 --> 00:32:32,418
Is that it?
Did you see a face?

460
00:32:34,386 --> 00:32:36,755
I couldn't see who it was,

461
00:32:36,788 --> 00:32:39,992
And it was only
for a split second.

462
00:32:43,462 --> 00:32:45,064
Suppose I was right.

463
00:32:45,097 --> 00:32:46,632
Suppose somebody
did kill her.

464
00:32:46,665 --> 00:32:48,500
I wanna catch the guy,
don't you?

465
00:32:48,534 --> 00:32:51,503
Yeah, but who would
wanna kill her?

466
00:32:51,537 --> 00:32:54,140
- I think it was Nick.
- Jodi, come on.

467
00:32:54,173 --> 00:32:56,675
Lisa completely
shut down his business.

468
00:32:56,708 --> 00:32:58,510
Nick was really mad.
We all saw it.

469
00:32:58,544 --> 00:33:00,446
Yeah, but Nick
wouldn't kill her.

470
00:33:00,479 --> 00:33:03,382
It was probably just
an accident like the cop said.

471
00:33:03,415 --> 00:33:06,585
I just...
I just can't accept that.

472
00:33:06,618 --> 00:33:09,221
The cops should be,
I don't know.

473
00:33:09,255 --> 00:33:11,423
They should be watching him.

474
00:33:21,300 --> 00:33:24,103
- Thank you.
- For what?

475
00:33:24,136 --> 00:33:27,106
For trying to help.

476
00:33:27,139 --> 00:33:29,075
I'm gonna go back to bed.

477
00:33:43,755 --> 00:33:48,026
So what do you think?
Yeah, they're in good condition.

478
00:33:49,128 --> 00:33:50,662
Where'd I get 'em?

479
00:33:50,696 --> 00:33:52,364
I stole 'em.
What kind of question is that?

480
00:33:52,398 --> 00:33:54,366
Do what you want.

481
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:56,302
You can melt 'em down,
sell 'em on the black market.

482
00:33:56,335 --> 00:34:00,506
I don't care.
Yeah, I'm coming right now.

483
00:34:07,346 --> 00:34:09,115
(Car alarm chirps)

484
00:34:10,249 --> 00:34:13,185
(Engine turns over)

485
00:34:44,683 --> 00:34:47,386
(Muffled dance music playing)

486
00:34:52,824 --> 00:34:54,893
