Yeah! Whoo!

487
00:34:54,926 --> 00:34:57,563
- Steve, what's up?
- Hey, what's up, Nick?

488
00:34:57,596 --> 00:34:59,698
- How are you, man?
- Good. You?

489
00:34:59,731 --> 00:35:01,767
- Good. Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

490
00:35:23,822 --> 00:35:25,857
Aww, man, really?

491
00:35:27,226 --> 00:35:28,894
(Clears throat)

492
00:35:28,927 --> 00:35:30,462
Driver's license, please.

493
00:35:30,496 --> 00:35:32,598
I forgot my ID.

494
00:35:35,801 --> 00:35:37,836
Turn around.

495
00:35:38,837 --> 00:35:41,207
Turn around.

496
00:35:51,983 --> 00:35:54,586
Okay. Come on in.

497
00:36:19,545 --> 00:36:21,213
So how's your car shop?

498
00:36:21,247 --> 00:36:23,615
Well, that's sort of
why I'm doing this.

499
00:36:23,649 --> 00:36:25,183
Looks like I gotta
shut it down.

500
00:36:36,828 --> 00:36:39,265
This way, Nicky.

501
00:36:44,736 --> 00:36:47,639
- Nick: Let's see.
- (zipper zings)

502
00:36:47,673 --> 00:36:49,375
Thank you.

503
00:36:52,578 --> 00:36:53,979
Nick: Perfect.

504
00:36:55,814 --> 00:36:57,349
Put this right here.

505
00:36:58,350 --> 00:36:59,918
Someone's looking for you.

506
00:37:02,020 --> 00:37:04,823
Hey, hey, come here!

507
00:37:04,856 --> 00:37:07,593
Hey, hey, hey.
Hey, I'm...

508
00:37:07,626 --> 00:37:09,828
What... Hey, I'm not
gonna hurt you.

509
00:37:09,861 --> 00:37:13,365
I'm your neighbor, okay?

510
00:37:13,399 --> 00:37:15,467
And why are
you following me?

511
00:37:15,501 --> 00:37:17,803
I'm not following you.
I come here a lot.

512
00:37:17,836 --> 00:37:20,439
Oh, okay.

513
00:37:20,472 --> 00:37:22,541
What's going on
back there?

514
00:37:22,574 --> 00:37:23,975
What do you think's
going on back there?

515
00:37:25,977 --> 00:37:29,648
- No, say it.
- You're selling her jewelry.

516
00:37:29,681 --> 00:37:31,350
Wait, what?
What do you mean?

517
00:37:31,383 --> 00:37:33,385
Lisa. You stole her jewelry
and now you're pawning it.

518
00:37:33,419 --> 00:37:35,454
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
I stole her jewelry?

519
00:37:35,487 --> 00:37:38,624
- I saw someone in her
house the other night.
- Oh, my God.

520
00:37:38,657 --> 00:37:40,959
You were mad at her because
she shut down your business
so you decided to get revenge.

521
00:37:40,992 --> 00:37:43,629
You sound just like that cop.
Why you talking to me like this?

522
00:37:43,662 --> 00:37:46,565
You snuck in, killed her,
stole her jewelry.

523
00:37:46,598 --> 00:37:50,536
- And now you're pawning it.
- (laughs) I killed her?

524
00:37:51,603 --> 00:37:53,572
Not only are you way...

525
00:37:53,605 --> 00:37:56,475
Off-base, but you are
incredibly obnoxious.

526
00:37:56,508 --> 00:37:57,809
- Am I?
- Yeah, you are,
but that's okay

527
00:37:57,843 --> 00:37:59,378
Because I kind of
have a crush on you.

528
00:37:59,411 --> 00:38:00,512
Oh, don't you try...

529
00:38:00,546 --> 00:38:02,648
(Clears throat)

530
00:38:02,681 --> 00:38:03,682
What did you say?

531
00:38:03,715 --> 00:38:05,451
You heard me.

532
00:38:09,688 --> 00:38:13,091
Hey, look, getting
my business shut down

533
00:38:13,124 --> 00:38:15,761
Is the best thing
that's ever happened to me.

534
00:38:15,794 --> 00:38:18,364
I mean, I got a job.

535
00:38:18,397 --> 00:38:21,667
Now I'm gonna be fixing cars
in a shop across town,
and I can't wait.

536
00:38:21,700 --> 00:38:26,605
I'm selling some
of my old tools to
a guy who works here.

537
00:38:27,706 --> 00:38:29,975
But...

538
00:38:30,008 --> 00:38:31,543
If you wanna believe

539
00:38:31,577 --> 00:38:35,347
That I killed her...

540
00:38:35,381 --> 00:38:37,483
Then go right ahead.

541
00:38:48,994 --> 00:38:51,463
So what, you're just...

542
00:38:51,497 --> 00:38:53,064
You're just gonna
stand there all night?

543
00:39:06,512 --> 00:39:08,346
They're gonna check your ID.

544
00:39:09,981 --> 00:39:12,651
What do I do?

545
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:16,688
*... this moment to arise

546
00:39:16,722 --> 00:39:19,858
* You take my breath away

547
00:39:19,891 --> 00:39:22,761
* I'm feeling cold

548
00:39:22,794 --> 00:39:27,666
* But I'm holding on

549
00:39:27,699 --> 00:39:32,604
* You turned
my world around *

550
00:39:35,173 --> 00:39:37,443
Hey, Borelli.
We need check the back.

551
00:39:37,476 --> 00:39:38,677
I'll show you.

552
00:39:41,713 --> 00:39:45,417
* Because of you

553
00:39:45,451 --> 00:39:49,755
* I know all the answers

554
00:39:49,788 --> 00:39:51,923
* Because of you

555
00:39:51,957 --> 00:39:56,161
* I'm taking all my chances

556
00:39:56,194 --> 00:39:58,730
* Because of you

557
00:39:58,764 --> 00:40:00,566
You should probably go.

558
00:40:00,599 --> 00:40:03,702
* Letting go of everything

559
00:40:03,735 --> 00:40:06,171
* I am

560
00:40:08,607 --> 00:40:12,678
* You take my
breath away... *

561
00:40:14,880 --> 00:40:18,083
Yeah, I'm sorry, Kristen.
Your aunt was murdered.

562
00:40:18,116 --> 00:40:22,921
Now with your permission,
I need to discuss
the autopsy results.

563
00:40:24,122 --> 00:40:25,757
Go ahead.

564
00:40:25,791 --> 00:40:27,759
As you can see,

565
00:40:27,793 --> 00:40:31,029
The impact to her
skull is quite severe.

566
00:40:31,062 --> 00:40:35,501
Now for a woman her height
falling less than four feet

567
00:40:35,534 --> 00:40:37,669
Hitting the side of
the tub at this angle,

568
00:40:37,703 --> 00:40:40,639
There is no way that
her skull would be
crushed to that degree.

569
00:40:40,672 --> 00:40:44,910
The physics of the
situation tells us this
was not a slip and fall.

570
00:40:44,943 --> 00:40:49,481
Something hit her
in the back of the head
with an incredible force.

571
00:40:49,515 --> 00:40:53,685
Now one scenario is that
the prowler entered the house
through an unlocked door.

572
00:40:53,719 --> 00:40:55,654
Lisa surprised him.
He killed her.

573
00:40:55,687 --> 00:40:57,989
He panicked and ran off
without stealing anything,

574
00:40:58,023 --> 00:41:01,860
Or she was murdered
for another reason.

575
00:41:01,893 --> 00:41:05,597
Now, Kristen,
we spoke to your church

576
00:41:05,631 --> 00:41:09,701
- regarding your whereabouts
at the time of her death.
- Wait, I'm a suspect?

577
00:41:09,735 --> 00:41:13,539
Well, your aunt made quite
a bit of money in Southern
California real estate.

578
00:41:13,572 --> 00:41:16,808
You're the sole
beneficiary in her will.

579
00:41:16,842 --> 00:41:19,144
So you're about to inherit
close to $4 million.

580
00:41:19,177 --> 00:41:20,812
I loved her more
than my own mother.

581
00:41:20,846 --> 00:41:23,214
Don't worry.
We confirmed your alibi.

582
00:41:23,248 --> 00:41:26,852
Several people in the church
said you were definitely
at the weekend retreat.

583
00:41:26,885 --> 00:41:28,987
I can't believe this.

584
00:41:29,020 --> 00:41:31,723
Detective,
who do you think did this?

585
00:41:31,757 --> 00:41:34,192
We don't know.
We talked to every
neighbor on the block.

586
00:41:34,225 --> 00:41:38,096
We contacted Lisa's friends
and her business associates.

587
00:41:38,129 --> 00:41:40,231
No one had anything bad
to say about her.

588
00:41:40,265 --> 00:41:43,168
Well, about the guy next door,
Nick Thompkin?

589
00:41:43,201 --> 00:41:46,738
Well, he said he was
home alone that night,

590
00:41:46,772 --> 00:41:48,173
But nobody could verify it.

591
00:41:48,206 --> 00:41:50,275
So he doesn't have an alibi.

592
00:41:50,308 --> 00:41:53,511
He could've done it.
He was really pissed
at my aunt. Right, Jodi?

593
00:41:56,882 --> 00:42:00,318
I don't...
I don't know about that.

594
00:42:00,351 --> 00:42:02,020
That's not what
you told me before.

595
00:42:02,053 --> 00:42:06,124
She's right, Jodi.
You said, and I quote,

596
00:42:06,157 --> 00:42:09,160
"Lisa called the cops on him.
Nick was really mad at her.

597
00:42:09,194 --> 00:42:14,132
If anybody from this
neighborhood would kill
her, it would be him."

598
00:42:14,165 --> 00:42:18,336
I just don't think he would
do something like that...

599
00:42:18,369 --> 00:42:21,139
- not anymore.
- So you're changing
your opinion.

600
00:42:21,172 --> 00:42:22,874
Yes.

601
00:42:22,908 --> 00:42:25,644
Can I ask why?

602
00:42:25,677 --> 00:42:27,646
I just have a feeling.

603
00:42:27,679 --> 00:42:28,980
A feeling?

604
00:42:29,014 --> 00:42:32,050
Okay, that's... that's unique.

605
00:42:32,083 --> 00:42:35,320
Wait, you're not gonna
arrest him because of
what I said, right?

606
00:42:35,353 --> 00:42:39,357
Well, we're not gonna
arrest anyone until we
have more evidence.

607
00:42:39,390 --> 00:42:42,761
Don't worry, Kristen.
We're not done yet.

608
00:42:42,794 --> 00:42:45,130
We're gonna get
whoever did this.

609
00:42:53,004 --> 00:42:56,174
Yeah, listen, I'm gonna need
to get a search warrant.

610
00:42:56,207 --> 00:42:59,010
His name is Nick Thompkin.

611
00:42:59,044 --> 00:43:03,815
The address is 1821...

612
00:43:34,045 --> 00:43:36,948
Hey, can I show you something?

613
00:43:36,982 --> 00:43:39,217
Sure.

614
00:43:39,250 --> 00:43:41,820
What do you think
they're talking about?

615
00:43:45,256 --> 00:43:48,259
I know exactly
what they're talking about.

616
00:43:48,293 --> 00:43:51,697
Ted would hit on me,
and Aunt Lisa didn't like it.

617
00:43:53,331 --> 00:43:56,301
Jodi, a lot of older guys
hit on me. So what?

618
00:43:56,334 --> 00:43:58,937
If they arrested every older guy
who tried to sleep with me,

619
00:43:58,970 --> 00:44:01,106
They'd have to start
building more prisons.

620
00:44:01,139 --> 00:44:03,208
Yeah, but look.

621
00:44:03,241 --> 00:44:06,044
- I mean, he's, like,
really mad at her.
- Jodi, stop it.

622
00:44:06,077 --> 00:44:08,914
- What?
- Just because someone gets
in an argument with my aunt

623
00:44:08,947 --> 00:44:11,683
Doesn't make them a killer.

624
00:44:11,717 --> 00:44:14,419
- What is with you?
- Okay, well, then who
do you think did it?

625
00:44:14,452 --> 00:44:19,324
I don't know.
I'm still trying to get past
the fact that she's gone.

626
00:44:20,959 --> 00:44:23,394
And this cop tells me
that she's been murdered

627
00:44:23,428 --> 00:44:25,463
And that I'm a suspect.

628
00:44:25,496 --> 00:44:29,400
Then you go around accusing
everyone in the neighborhood.
Maybe you did it.

629
00:44:29,434 --> 00:44:32,704
Jodi, I told you
to not bother her.

630
00:44:32,738 --> 00:44:36,307
She didn't do anything wrong.
(sighs)

631
00:44:36,341 --> 00:44:38,810
Kristen, I'm sorry.

632
00:44:42,213 --> 00:44:44,783
I'm just gonna go back home.

633
00:44:44,816 --> 00:44:48,954
Are you sure?
You're more than
welcome to stay.

634
00:44:52,223 --> 00:44:55,226
I'll let you know if
I can't handle it over there.

635
00:44:55,260 --> 00:44:57,262
Okay.

636
00:44:57,295 --> 00:44:59,364
Thank you for everything,
Ms. Allen.

637
00:45:05,136 --> 00:45:07,906
What did I tell you?

638
00:45:07,939 --> 00:45:10,108
Mom, will you just look
at this and tell me...

639
00:45:10,141 --> 00:45:12,043
- No!
- what you think?
Just please.

640
00:45:12,077 --> 00:45:14,712
- No, this is just
making it worse.
- Mom!

641
00:47:06,657 --> 00:47:08,626
Wait. Wait.

642
00:47:08,659 --> 00:47:10,395
We have a problem.

643
00:47:10,428 --> 00:47:12,430
The cops don't think
it was an accident.

644
00:47:13,932 --> 00:47:16,134
They think someone
killed her.

645
00:47:25,643 --> 00:47:27,445
You still think I killed her?

646
00:47:27,478 --> 00:47:29,314
I don't,

647
00:47:29,347 --> 00:47:32,417
But the cops think you did.

648
00:47:32,450 --> 00:47:35,120
You said you were
gonna make it look
like she slipped and fell.

649
00:47:35,153 --> 00:47:37,422
That's exactly what I did.

650
00:47:37,455 --> 00:47:39,925
Well, you hit
her at the wrong
angle or something.

651
00:47:39,958 --> 00:47:41,192
They figured it out.

652
00:47:41,226 --> 00:47:42,593
Well, maybe you
should've done it then.

653
00:47:42,627 --> 00:47:44,295
Baby, you know I
couldn't have done that.

654
00:47:44,329 --> 00:47:46,331
That's not what
we talked about.

655
00:47:46,364 --> 00:47:49,067
No, what we talked about
is I put her lights out
and then you give me half.

656
00:47:49,100 --> 00:47:51,369
- Where's the money?
- It's in probate.

657
00:47:51,402 --> 00:47:53,438
It's gonna take some time.
Just relax.

658
00:47:53,471 --> 00:47:56,041
Relax? Really?
How am I supposed to do that?

659
00:47:56,074 --> 00:47:57,976
- They're gonna figure out
what we did.
- No, they won't.

660
00:47:58,009 --> 00:48:00,045
Don't say that, baby.

661
00:48:00,078 --> 00:48:02,513
I'm tired of all
this sneaking around.

662
00:48:02,547 --> 00:48:04,482
Putting ten hours a day
into this lousy job.

663
00:48:04,515 --> 00:48:08,253
Do you really think I like
going to that church?
We have to act normal.

664
00:48:08,286 --> 00:48:10,188
Jodi: Look at the way
she's talking to him.

665
00:48:10,221 --> 00:48:12,690
Nick: Yeah, he looks really
mad at her about something.

666
00:48:12,723 --> 00:48:15,326
Well, I wanna go show Ted these
pictures and see what he says.

667
00:48:15,360 --> 00:48:17,963
I mean, I was hoping that
you would come with me.

668
00:48:17,996 --> 00:48:21,266
What? Now? I can't.
I'm starting that new job.

669
00:48:21,299 --> 00:48:23,301
If I don't hurry,
I'm gonna be late.

670
00:48:23,334 --> 00:48:25,503
If you don't keep it together,
you're going to ruin this.

671
00:48:25,536 --> 00:48:28,306
That girl across the street,
she's watching us.

672
00:48:28,339 --> 00:48:31,342
- What are you talking about?
- She's been taking pictures
of the entire neighborhood.

673
00:48:31,376 --> 00:48:33,644
Do you remember the argument
you had with my aunt?

674
00:48:33,678 --> 00:48:36,581
When you talk to her
the way that you do,

675
00:48:36,614 --> 00:48:40,151
Kristen doesn't understand
that you're just trying
to get in her pants, Ted.

676
00:48:40,185 --> 00:48:42,020
It is not what
you're thinking.

677
00:48:42,053 --> 00:48:44,022
It's exactly what I'm thinking,
and I don't like it.

678
00:48:44,055 --> 00:48:47,225
- Look...
- Stay away from her.
I mean it.

679
00:48:47,258 --> 00:48:50,361
Kristen: Jodi just
showed me pictures
of you arguing with Lisa.

680
00:48:50,395 --> 00:48:52,663
You look like you're ready
to rip her head off.

681
00:48:52,697 --> 00:48:56,301
Jodi's gonna show those
pictures to the cops.

682
00:48:56,334 --> 00:48:58,469
You're gonna have to
answer more questions.

683
00:48:58,503 --> 00:49:01,406
Okay. All right, well, that's
why we put together an alibi.

684
00:49:01,439 --> 00:49:04,509
Yeah, you see?
I went to the movies.
Got a ticket stub right here.

685
00:49:04,542 --> 00:49:06,444
We snuck out at 8:30.
I drove back here.

686
00:49:06,477 --> 00:49:08,246
Parked around the way
and nobody saw me.

687
00:49:08,279 --> 00:49:09,747
That would've worked if it
looked like it was an accident,

688
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:12,283
But now that it's murder,
it's not that simple.

689
00:49:12,317 --> 00:49:16,154
You're right. You're right.
Oh, I'm screwed.

690
00:49:16,187 --> 00:49:17,755
I mean, they're gonna
figure out I did this.

691
00:49:17,788 --> 00:49:20,992
No, baby, don't say that.
Look at me.

692
00:49:21,026 --> 00:49:23,494
I'm not gonna let
anything happen to you.

693
00:49:25,263 --> 00:49:27,999
I've got an idea.

694
00:49:28,033 --> 00:49:30,735
Let's go over to Ted's
later this afternoon
after I get home.

695
00:49:30,768 --> 00:49:33,304
- Okay.
- Then afterward we can
go to dinner or something.

696
00:49:33,338 --> 00:49:36,341
Well, just come
to my house when...

697
00:49:36,374 --> 00:49:38,143
Wait. Wait a sec.

698
00:49:39,777 --> 00:49:41,412
Did you just ask me out?

699
00:49:41,446 --> 00:49:43,114
Yeah.

700
00:49:44,282 --> 00:49:46,017
And you said yes.

701
00:50:40,171 --> 00:50:44,041
(Camera shutter clicking)

702
00:52:20,305 --> 00:52:21,639
This way.

703
00:52:28,846 --> 00:52:30,181
Here.

704
00:53:20,265 --> 00:53:21,732
(Gasps)

705
00:53:47,024 --> 00:53:48,859
Forget it. Let's go.

706
00:53:49,960 --> 00:53:51,596
Come on. Let's go.

707
00:54:00,905 --> 00:54:02,740
Jodi: Hey, Mom.
Can we talk?

708
00:54:02,773 --> 00:54:04,509
Yeah, sure.

709
00:54:08,879 --> 00:54:11,749
I think Kristen
and that guy Ted
killed Lisa.

710
00:54:13,017 --> 00:54:15,853
Oh, man.
First Nick
and now these two?

711
00:54:15,886 --> 00:54:17,355
I'm serious.

712
00:54:17,388 --> 00:54:20,858
Okay, what makes
you think that?

713
00:54:20,891 --> 00:54:22,927
What does this
look like to you?

714
00:54:22,960 --> 00:54:25,696
It looks like
they went hiking.

715
00:54:25,730 --> 00:54:29,867
Yes, I followed them to
the woods and they're, like,
totally into each other.

716
00:54:29,900 --> 00:54:31,669
They're having
an affair, Mom.

717
00:54:31,702 --> 00:54:33,738
Did you see them
get physical at all?

718
00:54:33,771 --> 00:54:36,341
No,

719
00:54:36,374 --> 00:54:39,477
But I saw him put
his arm around her
and then lean in.

720
00:54:39,510 --> 00:54:42,413
And then they went behind
a tree, so I don't know
if they kissed or not.

721
00:54:42,447 --> 00:54:44,482
So you can't say for sure?

722
00:54:44,515 --> 00:54:48,453
Still, what is a guy his
age doing in the woods
with someone like her?

723
00:54:48,486 --> 00:54:50,921
- Honey...
- I think I should show
these pictures to the police.

724
00:54:50,955 --> 00:54:53,991
No, you can't.
You were stalking them
with your camera.

725
00:54:54,024 --> 00:54:56,060
Remember what
Detective Franklin said?

726
00:54:56,093 --> 00:54:57,995
I was right about
the shadow, wasn't I?

727
00:54:58,028 --> 00:55:00,731
Yes, you were.
But this is pushing it,

728
00:55:00,765 --> 00:55:02,867
And these pictures don't
prove anything.

729
00:55:02,900 --> 00:55:04,902
What if you're wrong?

730
00:55:04,935 --> 00:55:07,405
What if Ted and
Kristen did kill Lisa?

731
00:55:08,806 --> 00:55:11,842
She was probably
attacked by a burglar

732
00:55:11,876 --> 00:55:14,512
- like the detective said.
- You're my mom.

733
00:55:14,545 --> 00:55:18,449
Why can't you just
back me up on this?
Why can't you believe me?

734
00:55:18,483 --> 00:55:22,353
Because you have accused
three of our neighbors
of being murder suspects.

735
00:55:22,387 --> 00:55:24,889
It's too much.

736
00:55:24,922 --> 00:55:27,592
Don't you see
what you're doing?

737
00:55:27,625 --> 00:55:31,596
You are inventing
a neighborhood boogeyman

738
00:55:31,629 --> 00:55:34,465
To punish your attacker.

739
00:55:34,499 --> 00:55:37,968
Honestly?

740
00:55:38,002 --> 00:55:40,070
I'm just worried
about Nick right now.

741
00:55:40,104 --> 00:55:42,440
The cops are looking at him
as their number one suspect,

742
00:55:42,473 --> 00:55:44,375
Partly because of what I said.

743
00:55:44,409 --> 00:55:46,711
And I know
he didn't do it.

744
00:55:50,147 --> 00:55:53,384
We should've done this earlier.
We're cutting it close.

745
00:55:53,418 --> 00:55:56,086
I'll watch the front.
Be careful.

746
00:56:16,140 --> 00:56:18,776
Come on.

747
00:56:23,748 --> 00:56:25,750
(Lock rattles)

748
00:56:46,771 --> 00:56:48,405
Damn it.

749
00:56:52,877 --> 00:56:54,211
Jodi:
Hey, how was work?

750
00:56:54,244 --> 00:56:56,046
Great.

751
00:57:05,089 --> 00:57:06,791
(Cell phone vibrates)

752
00:57:13,664 --> 00:57:15,466
It was really weird.

753
00:57:23,641 --> 00:57:26,844
- Nick: So we don't
have to talk to him?
- Jodi: Uh, no.

754
00:57:26,877 --> 00:57:30,515
Nick: Great. I just heard
from my dad and I gotta
go grab him at LAX.

755
00:57:30,548 --> 00:57:34,785
I talked to him yesterday.
I didn't think he'd
get here so quick.

756
00:57:34,819 --> 00:57:37,488
But maybe afterwards,
well, me and you

757
00:57:37,522 --> 00:57:39,924
Can go get dessert
or something.

758
00:57:39,957 --> 00:57:41,726
Okay.

759
00:57:45,262 --> 00:57:47,598
I wanna go
to the cops tomorrow,

760
00:57:47,632 --> 00:57:50,200
- (sighs)
- show them the pictures
and tell them everything.

761
00:57:50,234 --> 00:57:53,070
And I want you
to come with me.

762
00:57:53,103 --> 00:57:55,472
Why do you want me
to go with you?

763
00:57:56,907 --> 00:57:58,709
Because...

764
00:57:58,743 --> 00:58:01,712
I don't know.
I just think it might
help your case.

765
00:58:01,746 --> 00:58:04,682
Is that the only reason?

766
00:58:04,715 --> 00:58:07,518
What do you mean?
What other reason?

767
00:58:07,552 --> 00:58:09,854
Well, I just think that,

768
00:58:09,887 --> 00:58:11,789
That you like
hanging out with me.

769
00:58:11,822 --> 00:58:16,193
I just don't want you
to get arrested. That's all.

770
00:58:16,226 --> 00:58:18,929
So what, you're just,
like, doing all this,

771
00:58:18,963 --> 00:58:20,965
'Cause...

772
00:58:20,998 --> 00:58:22,232
'Cause you're
a concerned citizen?

773
00:58:22,266 --> 00:58:25,302
Something like that.

774
00:58:25,335 --> 00:58:27,504
No other reason?

775
00:58:29,840 --> 00:58:31,976
- No.
- You sure?

776
00:58:32,009 --> 00:58:34,545
I'm not sure

777
00:58:34,579 --> 00:58:37,181
About anything.

778
00:58:44,054 --> 00:58:46,056
(Sighs)

779
00:59:06,911 --> 00:59:10,748
You... you wanna go
into the living room?

780
00:59:10,781 --> 00:59:12,617
Don't you have to
pick up your dad?

781
00:59:12,650 --> 00:59:14,151
Not for like an hour.

782
00:59:14,184 --> 00:59:18,355
I mean, I-I-I should
probably get home.

783
00:59:18,388 --> 00:59:21,992
I mean, I've got work stuff.

784
00:59:22,026 --> 00:59:24,862
- Um...
- Yeah, yeah.

785
00:59:42,780 --> 00:59:45,015
(Cell phone rings)

786
00:59:45,049 --> 00:59:47,685
- It's Kristen.
- Oh, go ahead.

787
00:59:47,718 --> 00:59:51,021
- Hey, Kristen.
- Hey, Jodi.
Did I call at a bad time?

788
00:59:51,055 --> 00:59:53,858
- No.
- Can you come over?

789
00:59:53,891 --> 00:59:55,726
I really need to talk
to you about something.

790
00:59:55,760 --> 00:59:58,162
- Right now?
- Yeah, it's kind of important.

791
00:59:58,195 --> 01:00:01,298
Sure.
I'll be right over.

792
01:00:03,133 --> 01:00:06,804
- You gonna be okay?
- Mm-hmm.

793
01:00:06,837 --> 01:00:09,273
All right, so I guess
I'll see you tonight.

794
01:00:09,306 --> 01:00:11,008
Yeah.

795
01:00:11,041 --> 01:00:13,043
I'll walk you out.

796
01:00:24,388 --> 01:00:27,391
See you when you get back?

797
01:00:36,867 --> 01:00:38,402
All right.

798
01:00:45,242 --> 01:00:47,177
Hey, come on in.

799
01:00:49,279 --> 01:00:52,149
Jodi, I just wanted to apologize
for what I said today.

800
01:00:52,182 --> 01:00:54,785
Oh, I understand.
I know you got a lot
on your mind.

801
01:00:54,819 --> 01:00:58,823
I've been thinking about Nick.
I think you're right.

802
01:00:58,856 --> 01:01:01,458
- Why is that?
- Because of what
you said to the cop.

803
01:01:01,491 --> 01:01:03,894
- I mean, he did hate my aunt.
- No, I shouldn't
have said that.

804
01:01:03,928 --> 01:01:06,296
Jodi,
you understand people.

805
01:01:06,330 --> 01:01:09,066
- You see things
with your camera.
- I was wrong about him.

806
01:01:09,099 --> 01:01:11,769
Like I told the cops,
I just... I changed my mind.

807
01:01:11,802 --> 01:01:14,739
Why did you
change your mind?

808
01:01:16,106 --> 01:01:17,908
Why did you change yours?

809
01:01:20,210 --> 01:01:22,179
I saw you kissing him.

810
01:01:22,212 --> 01:01:24,481
You know, Jodi,

811
01:01:24,514 --> 01:01:27,084
Sex can cloud your judgment.

812
01:01:27,117 --> 01:01:30,087
Really? How?

813
01:01:30,120 --> 01:01:32,289
You know.

814
01:01:32,322 --> 01:01:34,291
No, I don't know.

815
01:01:34,324 --> 01:01:36,894
Why don't you
explain it to me?

816
01:01:36,927 --> 01:01:39,429
Wait. You're not still
a virgin, are you?

817
01:01:41,065 --> 01:01:42,232
- (Screams)
- (grunts)

818
01:01:42,266 --> 01:01:44,101
No, I'm not.

819
01:01:44,134 --> 01:01:48,973
Oh, my God.
Tell me all about him.
What is he like?

820
01:01:49,006 --> 01:01:52,309
He was a complete stranger.

821
01:01:52,342 --> 01:01:54,311
I never would've guessed.

822
01:01:54,344 --> 01:01:56,213
I mean, you seem
so sweet and innocent.

823
01:01:56,246 --> 01:01:58,515
I'll make a deal with you.

824
01:01:58,548 --> 01:02:02,820
I'll tell you who I'm
sleeping with, if you tell
me who you're sleeping with.

825
01:02:04,188 --> 01:02:07,357
I'm not sleeping
with anyone.

826
01:02:07,391 --> 01:02:09,393
I'm gonna save that
for marriage.

827
01:02:09,426 --> 01:02:11,228
Good luck with that.

828
01:02:19,904 --> 01:02:21,906
Thanks for coming over,
Jodi.

829
01:02:32,817 --> 01:02:34,451
I think she knows about us.

830
01:02:34,484 --> 01:02:35,953
Doesn't matter.

831
01:02:36,987 --> 01:02:39,123
We're in the clear.

832
01:02:39,156 --> 01:02:42,759
You are my everything.

833
01:02:55,139 --> 01:02:57,307
(Doorbell rings)

834
01:03:01,045 --> 01:03:04,381
Hi. I'm Jodi.
I live across the street.

835
01:03:04,414 --> 01:03:05,883
Is Nick here?

836
01:03:05,916 --> 01:03:08,853
Yeah. Come on in.

837
01:03:10,087 --> 01:03:12,456
I'm his dad Eddie.

838
01:03:12,489 --> 01:03:14,892
- It's nice to meet you.
- Nick, you got company.

839
01:03:14,925 --> 01:03:18,362
So you're the girl
who accused my son

840
01:03:18,395 --> 01:03:20,530
Of killing
the nice lady next door?

841
01:03:20,564 --> 01:03:23,167
- Well, actually...
- Let me tell you something.
You're wrong.

842
01:03:23,200 --> 01:03:25,335
I got the
greatest kid in the world.

843
01:03:25,369 --> 01:03:27,237
- Mr. Thompkin,
that's actually why I came.
- When he was this tall,

844
01:03:27,271 --> 01:03:29,406
He used to follow his mother
around helping her
with the housework,

845
01:03:29,439 --> 01:03:33,077
Scrubbing the floors.
Everybody he meets he tries
to do something good for them.

846
01:03:33,110 --> 01:03:35,545
- Talk to any of his friends.
- Dad, Dad.

847
01:03:35,579 --> 01:03:37,948
She gets it.
Thank you though.
Thank you. Thank you.

848
01:03:37,982 --> 01:03:40,384
I appreciate it.
Thanks. Great.

849
01:03:42,252 --> 01:03:44,488
Dad, aren't you,
like, jetlagged?

850
01:03:44,521 --> 01:03:49,326
- Don't you need
to sleep or something?
- Jetlag. I'm tired.

851
01:03:54,564 --> 01:03:57,601
- Hi.
- Hi.

852
01:03:57,634 --> 01:03:59,369
- Are you ready?
- Mm-hmm.

853
01:03:59,403 --> 01:04:00,837
All right, let's go.

854
01:04:06,143 --> 01:04:08,879
Wait. I forgot something.

855
01:04:17,421 --> 01:04:20,657
Mr. Thompkin, I have a court
order to search your premises.

856
01:04:20,690 --> 01:04:23,961
- Excuse me.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

857
01:04:23,994 --> 01:04:26,897
You guys take the back.

858
01:04:29,533 --> 01:04:31,668
- What's this?
- He's got a warrant.
I don't know.

859
01:04:31,701 --> 01:04:34,038
- Warrant?
- Yeah.

860
01:05:00,364 --> 01:05:03,000
- Can you explain this?
- I've never seen that before.

861
01:05:03,033 --> 01:05:06,370
Well, it looks like
blood and human hair.
Bag it.

862
01:05:06,403 --> 01:05:08,505
We're gonna take it down
to our lab to run
some tests on it

863
01:05:08,538 --> 01:05:10,574
Along with some other
items we found.

864
01:05:10,607 --> 01:05:12,709
- Someone must've
put that there.
- You're arresting him?

865
01:05:12,742 --> 01:05:15,679
We're gonna ask
him a few questions.
We got a lot to talk about.

866
01:05:15,712 --> 01:05:18,515
Nick, don't say anything
till we get an attorney.

867
01:05:18,548 --> 01:05:21,485
- Keep your mouth shut for once.
- Wait. No, no, no, Detective.

868
01:05:21,518 --> 01:05:23,487
I have to show you
some pictures, okay?

869
01:05:23,520 --> 01:05:25,522
He didn't do it.
It was Kristen.

870
01:05:25,555 --> 01:05:27,324
She's having an affair
with her neighbor Ted.

871
01:05:27,357 --> 01:05:29,960
Look, I followed them
into the woods.

872
01:05:29,994 --> 01:05:33,163
I think after they killed
Lisa, they buried the pipe

873
01:05:33,197 --> 01:05:35,565
And then dug it up
and planted it
in Nick's garage.

874
01:05:35,599 --> 01:05:37,667
Jodi, let's be honest
here, okay?

875
01:05:37,701 --> 01:05:40,204
I don't know if you're
saying this to protect
your boyfriend

876
01:05:40,237 --> 01:05:42,372
Or you're having another
one of your feelings.

877
01:05:42,406 --> 01:05:44,541
Neither one
of 'em are credible.

878
01:05:44,574 --> 01:05:46,977
Now if you'll excuse me.

879
01:06:09,666 --> 01:06:12,702
(Buzzer sounds)

880
01:06:12,736 --> 01:06:15,139
(Camera shutter clicking)

881
01:06:20,410 --> 01:06:23,080
Okay, Mr. Thompkin.
Thank you for letting me know.

882
01:06:23,113 --> 01:06:25,115
(Beeps)

883
01:06:26,783 --> 01:06:31,188
The blood on the pipe tested
positive for Lisa Miller's DNA.

884
01:06:31,221 --> 01:06:33,057
They arrested Nick.

885
01:06:35,692 --> 01:06:38,395
What was it doing
in his garage?

886
01:06:38,428 --> 01:06:40,697
Ted and Kristen
are framing him.

887
01:06:40,730 --> 01:06:43,533
What?

888
01:06:43,567 --> 01:06:45,769
- You don't think
he did it, do you?
- I don't know.

889
01:06:45,802 --> 01:06:48,805
But how can you be so
sure that he didn't do it?

890
01:06:48,838 --> 01:06:50,707
You don't know him
like I do.

891
01:06:50,740 --> 01:06:52,342
Honey, you met him
three weeks ago.

892
01:06:52,376 --> 01:06:54,144
You barely
know him yourself.

893
01:06:54,178 --> 01:06:57,181
Don't you think
I wanna believe you?

894
01:06:57,214 --> 01:07:00,317
But you're not looking
at the facts that
the police recovered.

895
01:07:00,350 --> 01:07:02,419
I know what I saw, Mom.

896
01:07:02,452 --> 01:07:06,490
I'm not gonna let Nick take
the fall for what they did.

897
01:07:06,523 --> 01:07:09,459
- (Sighs)
- Just come to the station
with me.

898
01:07:09,493 --> 01:07:11,495
I want you to hear it
from Nick.

899
01:07:15,765 --> 01:07:19,203
Nick:
Sure, I was pissed
at Mrs. Miller,

900
01:07:19,236 --> 01:07:23,507
But, then I realized she was
right, and I got over it.

901
01:07:23,540 --> 01:07:25,809
I wasn't mad at her anymore.

902
01:07:25,842 --> 01:07:28,145
What about your alibi?

903
01:07:28,178 --> 01:07:30,380
I was at home that night
watching a movie on TV.

904
01:07:30,414 --> 01:07:32,416
That's the truth.

905
01:07:32,449 --> 01:07:34,318
Ms. Allen,

906
01:07:34,351 --> 01:07:37,787
This isn't exactly the way
that I wanted to meet you,

907
01:07:37,821 --> 01:07:40,624
And I know it looks
really bad,

908
01:07:40,657 --> 01:07:43,560
But I swear

909
01:07:43,593 --> 01:07:45,695
I didn't kill her.

910
01:07:45,729 --> 01:07:49,099
Jodi brought me here
because she thought
you might say something

911
01:07:49,133 --> 01:07:51,535
To convince me
that you're innocent.

912
01:07:51,568 --> 01:07:54,371
- And I guess
that didn't happen.
- Mom, please.

913
01:07:54,404 --> 01:07:58,708
Nick, if you can't prove
to me that you didn't do it,

914
01:07:58,742 --> 01:08:01,278
How are you gonna
prove it to a jury?

915
01:08:03,913 --> 01:08:05,815
Maybe I can't.

916
01:08:05,849 --> 01:08:07,817
Maybe I'm gonna spend the next
50 years of my life in here.

917
01:08:07,851 --> 01:08:10,854
- Jodi: No.
- You know what I don't get?

918
01:08:10,887 --> 01:08:12,589
Is how you could...

919
01:08:13,790 --> 01:08:16,460
- Never mind.
- Andrea: What?

920
01:08:16,493 --> 01:08:18,628
Say it.

921
01:08:18,662 --> 01:08:21,165
You're her mother.

922
01:08:21,198 --> 01:08:23,233
What's your point?

923
01:08:23,267 --> 01:08:25,869
Jodi's smart,

924
01:08:25,902 --> 01:08:27,571
Courageous,

925
01:08:27,604 --> 01:08:30,440
Beautiful

926
01:08:30,474 --> 01:08:33,877
And she got all those
qualities from you.

927
01:08:33,910 --> 01:08:35,679
So I'm just trying
to understand

928
01:08:35,712 --> 01:08:38,348
How you can look her
in the eye right now

929
01:08:38,382 --> 01:08:43,119
And see that reflection
of yourself and not believe her.

930
01:08:47,491 --> 01:08:51,595
Okay, let's say for a minute
that you're right.

931
01:08:51,628 --> 01:08:55,232
There's still no proof
that Kristen and Ted did it.
Have you thought about that?

932
01:08:55,265 --> 01:08:59,303
Yes, I have been racking
my brain trying to
figure this out.

933
01:08:59,336 --> 01:09:03,240
I mean, talking to
Detective Franklin was no use.

934
01:09:03,273 --> 01:09:04,774
We've gotta try
something more.

935
01:09:04,808 --> 01:09:08,578
- Like what?
- (sighs)

936
01:09:08,612 --> 01:09:10,614
What about this?

937
01:09:10,647 --> 01:09:12,716
I'll follow Kristen
and you follow Ted.

938
01:09:12,749 --> 01:09:15,452
- No.
- Yes. Mom,
we'll get you a camera.

939
01:09:15,485 --> 01:09:17,921
- I mean, they're bound to make
a mistake eventually.
- Jodi!

940
01:09:17,954 --> 01:09:21,391
No. It'll only
cause more trouble.

941
01:09:21,425 --> 01:09:25,362
I'm sure that Nick's dad will
hire the best possible lawyer

942
01:09:25,395 --> 01:09:27,764
And if they need to get
a deposition from you,
they will.

943
01:09:27,797 --> 01:09:31,635
And in the meantime,
you are not gonna go
spying on them anymore.

944
01:09:31,668 --> 01:09:33,937
- You can't tell me what to do.
- Oh, yes, I can.

945
01:09:33,970 --> 01:09:36,740
And you're not
leaving the house
until you've calmed down.

946
01:09:36,773 --> 01:09:40,544
You're grounding me?
You've never done that before.

947
01:09:40,577 --> 01:09:42,379
Well, I'm doing it now.

948
01:09:52,021 --> 01:09:53,723
(Knock on door)

949
01:09:53,757 --> 01:09:56,993
Hi. You hungry?
I was gonna make
us some lunch.

950
01:09:57,026 --> 01:09:58,828
No, I'm okay.

951
01:09:58,862 --> 01:10:01,898
I'm just gonna finish
retouching this photo,

952
01:10:01,931 --> 01:10:05,402
But I'm kind of tired
so I'm just gonna lay
down for a little bit.

953
01:10:05,435 --> 01:10:06,836
Okay.

954
01:10:06,870 --> 01:10:10,707
- Hey, Mom.
- Yeah.

955
01:10:10,740 --> 01:10:13,443
I'm sorry about the way
I talked to you last night.

956
01:10:13,477 --> 01:10:16,846
Sweetie, it's okay.
We've had a rough
couple of weeks.

957
01:10:18,382 --> 01:10:19,716
- You want the door closed?
- Please.

958
01:10:19,749 --> 01:10:20,917
Okay.

959
01:10:50,447 --> 01:10:52,649
(Doorbell rings)

960
01:10:58,722 --> 01:11:00,557
- Hello.
- Hi.

961
01:11:00,590 --> 01:11:03,327
We haven't officially met.

962
01:11:03,360 --> 01:11:06,330
- No, I know who you are.
- Oh.

963
01:11:06,363 --> 01:11:09,466
Well, then you probably
know why I'm here.

964
01:11:10,967 --> 01:11:12,769
- Can I come in?
- I'm sorry.

965
01:11:12,802 --> 01:11:14,638
- I was just running
out the door.
- Look.

966
01:11:15,939 --> 01:11:18,007
Nick Thompkin is probably

967
01:11:18,041 --> 01:11:19,509
Gonna spend the rest
of his life in jail

968
01:11:19,543 --> 01:11:21,978
For something
that he didn't do.

969
01:11:22,011 --> 01:11:25,715
We're... we're
kind of together

970
01:11:25,749 --> 01:11:28,952
And he was arrested

971
01:11:28,985 --> 01:11:31,020
Before we could go
on an actual date.

972
01:11:31,054 --> 01:11:33,690
But, look, Mr. Wilcox,

973
01:11:33,723 --> 01:11:37,093
If there's anything that
you can do to help Nick,

974
01:11:37,126 --> 01:11:40,330
I'm... please...
I'm... I'm begging you.

975
01:11:40,364 --> 01:11:43,700
Jodi. That boy killed
a dear friend of mine.

976
01:11:43,733 --> 01:11:46,002
- I'm sorry. I've got
an appointment at the bank.
- Ow! I'm sorry.

977
01:11:46,035 --> 01:11:48,672
It's my contact.
It's out of place.

978
01:11:48,705 --> 01:11:52,909
Can I use your bathroom just
for a second, please?

979
01:11:52,942 --> 01:11:55,078
- (Sniffles)
- Of course.

980
01:11:55,111 --> 01:11:56,746
It's to the right.

981
01:12:19,102 --> 01:12:21,104
Thank you.
It was nice to meet you.

982
01:12:21,137 --> 01:12:22,706
Yes, a pleasure.

983
01:12:33,983 --> 01:12:36,119
(Engine turns over)

984
01:14:19,856 --> 01:14:22,526
Hey, sweetie.
I brought you some food.

985
01:14:24,828 --> 01:14:26,696
Jodi?

986
01:14:26,730 --> 01:14:28,632
- (Knocks)
- Jodi?

987
01:14:28,665 --> 01:14:30,133
(Door rattles)

988
01:14:30,166 --> 01:14:31,167
Jodi?

989
01:14:46,816 --> 01:14:48,752
- Hey, baby.
- Hey.

990
01:14:48,785 --> 01:14:50,854
Mmm, bank account is open.

991
01:14:50,887 --> 01:14:53,657
Good, 'cause I've got
something to show you.

992
01:14:59,128 --> 01:15:01,998
- Ted: Surprise?
- Uh-huh.

993
01:15:03,967 --> 01:15:06,035
- 50 grand.
- (sighs)

994
01:15:06,069 --> 01:15:07,637
Where'd you get that?

995
01:15:07,671 --> 01:15:09,105
The college fund she left me.

996
01:15:09,138 --> 01:15:11,541
Her money's starting
to roll in.

997
01:15:11,575 --> 01:15:13,743
Perfect.
It's all working out.

998
01:15:14,978 --> 01:15:16,713
Yes, it's incredible.

999
01:15:16,746 --> 01:15:20,016
We're gonna leave here
and we're gonna get
our beach house.

1000
01:15:20,049 --> 01:15:22,886
- Everything we've
always wanted.
- Everything.

1001
01:15:22,919 --> 01:15:27,523
- I've got
something else for you.
- Oh, do you? (Laughs)

1002
01:15:48,645 --> 01:15:50,213
Jodi!

1003
01:16:02,692 --> 01:16:04,828
Relax.

1004
01:16:10,299 --> 01:16:13,236
Ted: Baby... (laughs)

1005
01:16:13,269 --> 01:16:14,704
(Gasps)

1006
01:16:14,738 --> 01:16:17,607
Whatever did I do

1007
01:16:17,641 --> 01:16:19,342
To deserve you?

1008
01:16:19,375 --> 01:16:20,910
(Gunshot)

1009
01:16:26,683 --> 01:16:29,252
(Panting)

1010
01:16:51,775 --> 01:16:52,809
(Beeping)

1011
01:17:18,401 --> 01:17:20,970
- Hi, this is Jodi.
Leave a message.
- (beeps)

1012
01:17:21,004 --> 01:17:23,673
Where are you?
I am really worried right now.

1013
01:17:23,707 --> 01:17:25,341
- Call me back.
- (beeps)

1014
01:17:29,178 --> 01:17:31,047
Get in. You're driving.

1015
01:17:35,118 --> 01:17:36,820
Give me your phone.

1016
01:17:37,954 --> 01:17:39,756
Give me your phone.

1017
01:17:42,258 --> 01:17:43,827
(Doorbell rings)

1018
01:17:58,474 --> 01:18:00,409
(Beeps)

1019
01:18:02,011 --> 01:18:06,482
- Go. Go!
- (engine turns over)

1020
01:18:06,515 --> 01:18:08,785
- Hi, this is Jodi.
Leave a message.
- (beeps)

1021
01:18:08,818 --> 01:18:11,020
Jodi, you need to tell
me you're all right.

1022
01:18:11,054 --> 01:18:13,422
- I'm at Kristen's
front door right now.
- (bell ringing)

1023
01:18:21,898 --> 01:18:25,835
What the hell are you doing
driving Ted's car?

1024
01:18:25,869 --> 01:18:28,237
(Beeps)

1025
01:18:28,271 --> 01:18:30,940
(Thinking)
First Nick and now these two?

1026
01:18:30,974 --> 01:18:32,842
What is a guy his age
doing in the woods
with someone like her?

1027
01:18:32,876 --> 01:18:34,844
These pictures don't
prove anything.

1028
01:18:34,878 --> 01:18:38,247
What if you're wrong?
What if Ted and Kristen
did kill Lisa?

1029
01:18:50,293 --> 01:18:52,495
Don't go too fast.

1030
01:18:52,528 --> 01:18:54,397
They're gonna know
you killed Ted.

1031
01:18:56,199 --> 01:18:58,534
What was that,
detective?

1032
01:18:58,567 --> 01:19:01,504
Did I hear the gunshot
from Ted's house?

1033
01:19:01,537 --> 01:19:03,807
No, I didn't.

1034
01:19:07,410 --> 01:19:09,946
Suicide, oh, my God,
that's so tragic.

1035
01:19:09,979 --> 01:19:13,182
I know he loved
his wife very much.

1036
01:19:13,216 --> 01:19:14,984
He was really distraught
when she left him.

1037
01:19:17,320 --> 01:19:19,956
(Laughs)

1038
01:19:27,430 --> 01:19:28,497
Keep going straight.

1039
01:19:45,114 --> 01:19:46,415
Man:
9-1-1. What's your emergency?

1040
01:19:46,449 --> 01:19:48,384
I think my daughter
is being kidnapped.

1041
01:19:56,392 --> 01:19:59,028
Ma'am, when they come
to a stop, call us back
and tell us where you are.

1042
01:19:59,062 --> 01:20:01,464
We'll dispatch someone
right away.

1043
01:20:01,497 --> 01:20:04,433
- That might be too late.
- We will get there as soon
as we can, ma'am.

1044
01:20:04,467 --> 01:20:06,069
(Sighs)

1045
01:20:08,337 --> 01:20:10,239
Exit up here.

1046
01:20:24,353 --> 01:20:25,855
That dirt road up ahead.
Pull over there.

1047
01:20:59,422 --> 01:21:00,990
Get out.

1048
01:21:03,226 --> 01:21:05,228
This way. Go.

1049
01:21:34,490 --> 01:21:35,992
Stop.

1050
01:21:37,726 --> 01:21:39,996
Put your camera down.

1051
01:21:47,136 --> 01:21:49,338
Smash it.

1052
01:21:57,313 --> 01:21:59,983
I told everyone you
and Ted were hiking
out here.

1053
01:22:00,016 --> 01:22:01,684
Shut up and do what I say.

1054
01:22:01,717 --> 01:22:03,987
- You're gonna bury me?
- Do it!

1055
01:22:18,367 --> 01:22:20,636
Now start digging.

1056
01:23:06,315 --> 01:23:09,218
(Shouts)
Oh, my God!

1057
01:23:09,252 --> 01:23:11,754
(Grunting)

1058
01:23:15,124 --> 01:23:17,726
(Gagging)

1059
01:23:36,312 --> 01:23:39,315
(Coughing)

1060
01:23:54,863 --> 01:23:58,134
- Baby, come here.
- Mom, are you okay?

1061
01:23:58,167 --> 01:24:00,403
Andrea: Yeah.

1062
01:24:00,436 --> 01:24:03,306
(Panting)

1063
01:24:16,152 --> 01:24:18,187
Kristen:
Her money's starting
to roll in.

1064
01:24:18,221 --> 01:24:19,455
Ted:
It's all working out.

1065
01:24:19,488 --> 01:24:21,157
I've got something
else for you.

1066
01:24:21,190 --> 01:24:23,092
- Oh, do you?
- Uh-huh.

1067
01:24:23,126 --> 01:24:25,428
- (Gunshot)
- (gasps)

1068
01:24:30,599 --> 01:24:32,135
Congratulations.

1069
01:24:41,744 --> 01:24:42,845
Thanks.

1070
01:25:10,239 --> 01:25:14,143
Jodi: A lot of people
have asked me why we moved
to this neighborhood.

1071
01:25:14,177 --> 01:25:17,713
Three months ago I was alone
in our condo and this
man broke in.

1072
01:25:17,746 --> 01:25:21,850
He messed me up pretty bad,
and it was even worse
for my mom

1073
01:25:21,884 --> 01:25:25,788
Because she saw the whole
thing, but she couldn't
do anything to stop him.

1074
01:25:25,821 --> 01:25:29,558
So we decided
to leave the city.

1075
01:25:29,592 --> 01:25:31,527
My mom sold the condo.

1076
01:25:31,560 --> 01:25:34,530
We packed up
and here we are.

1077
01:25:34,563 --> 01:25:37,400
And that is the official
reason why we moved here.

1078
01:25:41,370 --> 01:25:43,839
I'm glad you told me.

1079
01:25:43,872 --> 01:25:45,708
I was afraid to.

1080
01:25:47,243 --> 01:25:49,445
You got nothing
to worry about.

1081
01:25:51,514 --> 01:25:53,182
Know what I think?

1082
01:25:53,216 --> 01:25:55,351
What?

1083
01:25:55,384 --> 01:25:58,354
I think the real reason
I moved here

1084
01:25:58,387 --> 01:26:00,523
Is because...

1085
01:26:03,226 --> 01:26:04,560
I really need
a good mechanic.

1086
01:26:04,593 --> 01:26:06,962
My car has been making
this weird noise.

1087
01:26:06,995 --> 01:26:08,897
Can you help me out?

1088
01:26:20,509 --> 01:26:21,910
(Camera shutter clicks)

1089
01:26:26,949 --> 01:26:29,952
(Music playing)

